item.description:
This workflow is used to build a factory default template to move the vSmart from CLI mode to vManage mode. This must be completed before applying a vSmart policy.

first, get all feature templates, and feed feed IDs into the body for building device template. The pre-built body contains the template IDs in the DevNet reservable sandbox, but you can manually edit those.

Given the templateId and the vSmart UUID (from the vSmart device list), you feed this into the "attach template" process. This returns a "push_feature" ID in response which you can query for status until complete.

You can validate proper template attached by ensuring the vSmarts are now in vManage mode.

response.name: Success
Success
Success
Success
Success

In progress
Success

item.description:
Builds a simple policy using a subset of sites, a single full-mesh VPN, and a voice SLA class matching DSCP 46 to prefer MPLS over Internet.

First, create a site, VPN, and SLA class object, each of which will return a listId.

The site and VPN IDs feed into the mesh topology, which returns a definitionId.

The SLA class ID feeds into "approute" under the slaClass "ref" to build an app-aware routing policy. This policy also has a definitionId.

Adding a vSmart policy requires the site/vpn listId, approute definitionId, and mesh definitionId (does not need the sla ID). A successful request has no request.

You can issue the "get policy vsmart" to retrieve the policyId. This can be used in the activation URL, which returns another ID.

The ID returned from activation can be required for status until complete.
